article.headline: Manhattan 86, Canisius 77
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- C.J. Anderson scored 25 points to lift Manhattan to a 86-77 victory over Canisius on Thursday night. Anderson also grabbed 16 rebounds while shooting 12 of 23 from the field. Peter Mulligan added 22 points and had six rebounds for the Jaspers (9-6, 4-3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Arturo Dubois and Jeff Xavier each scored 13 points. Canisius (5-11, 3-4) lost for only the second time in its last six games while Manhattan won its sixth straight against the Golden Griffins. Jon Popofski led Canisius with 23 points. Kevin Downey added 20. Manhattan led 45-39 at halftime and held a 13-point advantage in the second half before Canisius mounted a late 11-5 run to close within a point on Popofski's 3-pointer with 1:26 remaining. Manhattan pulled away late at the foul line as Mulligan sank 5 of 6 free throws in the final seconds. The Jaspers shot 51.5 percent from the field while out rebounding Canisius 43-29.
